              "name": "Cleanse",
              "type": "spell",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=29380/cleanse"
            },
            {
              "id": 1044,
              "name": "Blessing of Freedom",
              "type": "spell",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=1044/blessing-of-freedom"
            },
            {
              "id": 27137,
              "name": "Flash of Light",
              "type": "spell",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=27137"
            }
          ],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Holy Paladin Healer in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [
            {
              "href": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=29380/cleanse",
              "text": "Cleanse"
            },
            {
              "href": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=1044/blessing-of-freedom",
              "text": "Blessing of Freedom"
            },
            {
              "href": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=27137",
              "text": ""
            }
          ],
          "text": "As your best leveling strategy is being with a questing partner or a dungeon group, there are a few tips to keep in mind. First, full utilization of spells like Cleanse and Blessing of Freedom will provide the best results when leveling through TBC Classic. It's easy to fall into the trap of spamming , but the Paladin toolkit is massive, and using each spell is paramount to your success."
        },
        {
          "entities": [
            {
              "id": 13444,
              "name": "Major Mana Potion",
              "type": "item",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/item=13444/major-mana-potion"
            },
            {
              "id": 22832,
              "name": "Super Mana Potion",
              "type": "item",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/item=22832/super-mana-potion"
            },
            {
              "id": 28399,
              "name": "Filtered Draenic Water",
              "type": "item",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/item=28399/filtered-draenic-water"
            },
            {
              "id": 21177,
              "name": "Symbol of Kings",
              "type": "item",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/item=21177/symbol-of-kings"
            }
          ],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Holy Paladin Healer in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [
            {
              "href": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/item=13444/major-mana-potion",
              "text": "Major Mana Potion"
            },
            {
              "href": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/item=22832/super-mana-potion",
              "text": "Super Mana Potion"
            },
            {
              "href": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/item=28399/filtered-draenic-water",
              "text": "Filtered Draenic Water"
            },
            {
              "href": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/item=21177/symbol-of-kings",
              "text": "Symbol of Kings"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Be ready with consumables. Nothing slows down a run quicker than having to stop and drink (or worse, resurrect someone) because you ran out of mana. Keeping a steady supply of Major Mana Potion / Super Mana Potion and water (like Filtered Draenic Water ) is vital to maintaining an efficient run. Don't forget about your Symbol of Kings either!"
        },
        {
          "entities": [],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Holy Paladin Healer in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [],
          "text": "Use this time as you level up to practice downranking some of your heals. While it won't be necessary, it's a good idea to understand the fundamentals of rotating through a few different ranks of your healing spells to get a grasp of how to conserve mana and anticipate incoming damage with appropriately sized heals."
        },
        {
          "entities": [],
          "level_range": null,
          "section": "Leveling Tips for Holy Paladin Healer in TBC Classic",
          "source_links": [],
          "text": "Because the initial levels are relatively easy, there isn't a whole lot of emphasis on building out a specific set of gear or even a strict talent build due to how Paladin healing works. Technically, you could level as Retribution and just throw on any pieces of +healing and intellect gear you have and do fine through the first 40 or so levels without any noticeable difference. Because of this, you may find it better to level while rotating through all three playstyles: tanking, healing, and DPSing. Not only will this make things easier if you decide to try a dungeon, but it will also help you understand the class better and determine what specializations you enjoy playing."
        },
        {
          "entities": [
            {
              "id": 498,
              "name": "Divine Protection",
              "type": "spell",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=498/divine-protection"
            },
            {
              "id": 7328,
              "name": "Redemption",
              "type": "spell",
              "url": "https://www.wowhead.com/tbc/spell=7328/redemption"
